1
00:03:47,155 --> 00:03:48,905
Think of it, Thing.

2
00:03:50,491 --> 00:03:52,531
For 25 years,

3
00:03:52,702 --> 00:03:55,582
we've attempted to contact Fester
in the great beyond,

4
00:03:55,746 --> 00:03:58,416
and for 25 years,

5
00:03:58,916 --> 00:03:59,956
nothing.

6
00:04:01,419 --> 00:04:04,879
I'm beginning to think
my brother truly is lost.

7
00:04:15,224 --> 00:04:18,144
Don't be a baby. I know what I'm doing.

8
00:04:21,272 --> 00:04:22,482
Help me.

9
00:04:35,286 --> 00:04:36,746
Look at her.

10
00:04:37,622 --> 00:04:39,792
I would die for her.

11
00:04:40,791 --> 00:04:42,581
I would kill for her.

12
00:04:44,086 --> 00:04:45,706
Either way, what bliss.

13
00:04:52,386 --> 00:04:55,596
- Unhappy, darling?
- Oh, yes.

14
00:04:56,766 --> 00:04:58,386
Yes, completely.

15
00:05:06,526 --> 00:05:07,726
Gomez,

16
00:05:09,278 --> 00:05:10,568
the sun.

17
00:05:13,241 --> 00:05:16,741
Oh, Tish, that's French.

18
00:05:17,119 --> 00:05:18,159
Oui.

19
00:05:20,456 --> 00:05:21,496
Cara Mia.

20
00:05:25,169 --> 00:05:27,879
En Garde, monsieur Soleil.

21
00:05:30,508 --> 00:05:31,758
Gomez?

22
00:05:32,134 --> 00:05:33,184
Querida.

23
00:05:33,511 --> 00:05:36,561
Last night you were unhinged.

24
00:05:37,557 --> 00:05:40,387
You were like some
desperate howling demon.

25
00:05:40,935 --> 00:05:42,635
You frightened me.

26
00:05:44,814 --> 00:05:46,234
Do it again.

27
00:05:53,531 --> 00:05:55,201
Thank you, Lurch.

28
00:06:32,737 --> 00:06:34,447
Damn you, Addams!

29
00:06:34,864 --> 00:06:36,744
Sorry about the window, Judge.

30
00:06:36,907 --> 00:06:39,617
Keep the ball. I have a whole bucketful.

31
00:06:43,748 --> 00:06:45,418
You moron!

32
00:06:49,587 --> 00:06:51,497
It is a milestone, Tish.

33
00:06:51,672 --> 00:06:54,262
This very night, our 25th séance.

34
00:06:55,926 --> 00:06:59,346
All those years, gnawed by guilt,

35
00:07:00,222 --> 00:07:01,812
undone by woe,

36
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:05,770
burning with uncertainty.

37
00:07:07,813 --> 00:07:10,023
Don't torture yourself, Gomez.

38
00:07:11,817 --> 00:07:13,317
That's my job.

39
00:07:14,862 --> 00:07:16,612
Oh, Tish.

40
00:07:17,782 --> 00:07:20,452
Imagine, darling,
if Fester did come back.

41
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:24,790
Half alive, barely human,
a rotting shell.

42
00:07:25,456 --> 00:07:26,916
Don't tease.

43
00:07:40,012 --> 00:07:41,932
Stop it! I'm warning you.

44
00:07:47,978 --> 00:07:49,768
Look, darling. Tully is here.

45
00:07:51,524 --> 00:07:53,784
- Tully!
- Romping with Gate.

46
00:07:56,112 --> 00:07:58,822
These are your last paying clients,
may I remind you?

47
00:07:58,989 --> 00:08:01,369
- If it gives you pleasure.
- Something has to.

48
00:08:01,534 --> 00:08:04,744
Like a decent coat,
something dressy, for evening.

49
00:08:05,162 --> 00:08:06,872
Ask for a loan. Beg!

50
00:08:07,039 --> 00:08:09,039
No loans. I am not a bum.

51
00:08:09,333 --> 00:08:11,713
Don't say it. I'll get the money.

52
00:08:11,877 --> 00:08:13,167
I have a plan.

53
00:08:13,671 --> 00:08:15,341
This is all so humiliating.

54
00:08:15,506 --> 00:08:18,586
- Why did I marry you?
- Because I said yes.

55
00:08:19,218 --> 00:08:22,888
I'm here to see Mrs. Addams
about the charity auction.

56
00:08:25,474 --> 00:08:27,064
Stop! Let go!

57
00:08:51,375 --> 00:08:53,205
- Missed!
- What's that?

58
00:09:00,217 --> 00:09:02,087
Dirty pool, old man.

59
00:09:02,762 --> 00:09:04,102
I like it.

60
00:09:15,941 --> 00:09:17,321
Had enough?

61
00:09:23,449 --> 00:09:24,989
Where's my pen?

62
00:09:25,951 --> 00:09:28,241
Never mind. I'll take yours.

63
00:09:35,586 --> 00:09:37,546
First, the old business.

64
00:09:39,089 --> 00:09:42,049
Charity auction, it's ridiculous!

65
00:09:43,594 --> 00:09:46,814
- Perhaps it's in here.
- I don't think so.

66
00:09:53,062 --> 00:09:55,612
"Uncle Niknak's winter wardrobe."

67
00:10:01,487 --> 00:10:03,947
"Uncle Niknak's summer wardrobe."

68
00:10:07,243 --> 00:10:08,793
"Uncle Niknak."

69
00:10:11,413 --> 00:10:14,753
"The Fester Addams
Offshore Retirement Fund?"

70
00:10:15,251 --> 00:10:17,921
- What would it do?
- What wouldn't it do?

71
00:10:18,087 --> 00:10:20,957
Fester, all tribute to thee.

72
00:10:21,131 --> 00:10:23,761
- Some called him inhumanly evil.
- No!

73
00:10:23,926 --> 00:10:26,926
Only our parents. I called him brother.

74
00:10:27,096 --> 00:10:30,766
And his memory must live on forever
through money.

75
00:10:31,141 --> 00:10:34,441
I'm gonna deposit the funds
under my name for tax purposes.

76
00:10:34,603 --> 00:10:35,813
That's inspired.

77
00:10:35,980 --> 00:10:39,270
He would've wanted it that way.
Beloved Fester.

78
00:10:41,277 --> 00:10:42,567
Indeed!

79
00:10:44,154 --> 00:10:46,614
- For Fester!
- For Fester! A brother!

80
00:10:46,782 --> 00:10:48,202
- My brother!
- One of a kind!

81
00:10:48,367 --> 00:10:51,407
- The doctors all said...
- Kind to animals, so good with children!

82
00:10:51,579 --> 00:10:54,409
- They never proved anything.
- $1 million is the perfect amount.

83
00:10:54,582 --> 00:10:57,042
- It's brilliant.
- It's untraceable!

84
00:10:59,920 --> 00:11:02,130
But, Tully, it's not old business.

85
00:11:02,298 --> 00:11:04,818
It's going to have to wait.
You know the rules better than that.

86
00:11:04,925 --> 00:11:08,385
Why? But this is different.
This is in my name. Make an exception!

87
00:11:08,554 --> 00:11:11,434
Old business is old business
and new business is new business

88
00:11:11,599 --> 00:11:12,929
and this is new business

89
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:15,980
and we do not discuss
new business until

90
00:11:20,149 --> 00:11:21,649
next quarter.

91
00:11:21,817 --> 00:11:25,027
Next quarter?

92
00:11:27,406 --> 00:11:31,486
Fine lunge, but your riposte,
a tad rusty.

93
00:11:35,831 --> 00:11:37,251
Make yourself comfortable, old man,

94
00:11:37,416 --> 00:11:40,496
while I get the money
for the monthly expenses.

95
00:12:04,109 --> 00:12:07,609
There it is.
Just what we've been searching for.

96
00:12:08,614 --> 00:12:10,244
Thank you, Thing.

97
00:12:12,493 --> 00:12:15,583
My God, what is it?

98
00:12:15,913 --> 00:12:18,543
A finger trap
from the court of Emperor Wu.

99
00:12:18,707 --> 00:12:20,827
It must be worth a fortune.

100
00:12:21,585 --> 00:12:26,085
Oh, Morticia! This is too extravagant!

101
00:12:27,675 --> 00:12:29,045
Even for the auction.

102
00:12:29,760 --> 00:12:31,260
Let's keep it.

103
00:12:31,762 --> 00:12:36,182
Hush, Mama. It's for charity.
Widows and orphans.

104
00:12:36,934 --> 00:12:38,774
We need more of them.

105
00:12:40,020 --> 00:12:41,270
Margaret?

106
00:12:42,690 --> 00:12:44,690
About the séance tonight.

107
00:12:45,442 --> 00:12:49,362
I wish you'd come. It's Gomez,
I'm terribly worried about him.

108
00:12:50,239 --> 00:12:52,739
He won't eat. He can't sleep.

109
00:12:53,742 --> 00:12:55,912
He keeps coughing up blood.

110
00:12:56,829 --> 00:12:58,579
He coughs up blood?

111
00:12:59,873 --> 00:13:01,963
Well, not like he used to.

112
00:13:05,671 --> 00:13:07,091
Down, kitty!

113
00:13:42,583 --> 00:13:45,133
There, the monthly expenses.

114
00:13:54,136 --> 00:13:55,636
Miss Bradbury.

115
00:13:58,640 --> 00:14:00,100
Miss Bradbury!

116
00:14:00,267 --> 00:14:04,727
- She's gone home, Mr. Alford.
- Oh, Mrs. Craven!

117
00:14:05,689 --> 00:14:08,979
- I was just about to call you.
- I'm certain you were.

118
00:14:09,151 --> 00:14:12,531
You haven't met my son Gordon,
have you, Mr. Alford?

119
00:14:13,614 --> 00:14:14,784
Hello.

120
00:14:17,951 --> 00:14:21,871
Is this the one, Mother?
That deadbeat you mentioned?

121
00:14:23,707 --> 00:14:25,018
No, wait, wait. Wait, wait, wait.

122
00:14:25,042 --> 00:14:28,252
Hold on. Hold on. Hold on.
You have to listen to me.

123
00:14:28,420 --> 00:14:31,050
Do we, Mr. Alford? And why?

124
00:14:31,465 --> 00:14:33,255
Please, hear me out!

125
00:14:34,885 --> 00:14:36,295
Hear me out!

126
00:14:36,595 --> 00:14:38,635
Please. Please!

127
00:14:39,932 --> 00:14:41,182
Your call, Mother.

128
00:14:41,350 --> 00:14:44,640
Gordon and I
enjoy a very special relationship.

129
00:14:44,812 --> 00:14:47,612
- She's a pip!
- Refreshing, no?

130
00:14:47,773 --> 00:14:49,733
- Down, Gordon.
- Mother?

131
00:14:49,900 --> 00:14:51,480
- Gordon.
- Gordon!

132
00:14:54,029 --> 00:14:57,819
We've lent you a considerable sum,
many thousands of dollars.

133
00:14:58,075 --> 00:14:59,075
Payment due.

134
00:14:59,243 --> 00:15:01,554
I don't have the money to repay you.
I've tried everything.

135
00:15:01,578 --> 00:15:05,368
- Oh, Gordon, I want to believe him.
- So do I.

136
00:15:05,541 --> 00:15:06,711
Make me proud.

137
00:15:06,875 --> 00:15:08,575
No, no, no, no, no.

138
00:15:16,635 --> 00:15:19,795
- He lied to us, Mother.
- No, no. It's not what you think.

139
00:15:19,972 --> 00:15:22,062
Those are doubloons
for the Addams account.

140
00:15:22,224 --> 00:15:23,274
Addams?

141
00:15:23,433 --> 00:15:25,813
There's more, there's a fortune,
but nobody can get to it.

142
00:15:25,978 --> 00:15:27,098
Don't you think I've tried?

143
00:15:27,271 --> 00:15:29,941
Have you? Have you tried hard enough?

144
00:15:30,107 --> 00:15:33,777
- Ask him, sweetheart.
- No, no, no, sweetheart. Don't ask.

145
00:15:41,910 --> 00:15:43,120
Fester.

146
00:15:49,793 --> 00:15:52,753
- It's a miserable night.
- I know, darling.

147
00:15:53,463 --> 00:15:55,053
Séance weather.

148
00:15:56,425 --> 00:15:58,755
Children, we're starting!

149
00:15:59,094 --> 00:16:01,054
Put down that antenna.

150
00:16:07,895 --> 00:16:11,685
It's unbelievable.
This hideous creature and my little boy.

151
00:16:15,068 --> 00:16:16,858
They could be twins.

152
00:16:17,529 --> 00:16:21,119
But they're his family. What
makes you think they'll fall for it?

153
00:16:21,283 --> 00:16:23,993
You shave your head, we dress you up.
No problem.

154
00:16:24,161 --> 00:16:26,139
They'll think he's Fester,
their long-lost brother.

155
00:16:26,163 --> 00:16:28,163
I hope so, Mr. Alford, for your sake.

156
00:16:28,332 --> 00:16:30,252
Hey, I've been the Addams' lawyer
for years.

157
00:16:30,417 --> 00:16:32,497
- They're morons.
- Obviously.

158
00:16:32,669 --> 00:16:35,023
- Now what about the gold?
- They got this vault, it's somewhere...

159
00:16:35,047 --> 00:16:36,627
- Where?
- I'm not sure.

160
00:16:36,798 --> 00:16:38,668
That's a problem, isn't it?

161
00:16:38,842 --> 00:16:41,552
Now listen,
Fester's been missing for 25 years.

162
00:16:41,720 --> 00:16:43,430
He and Gomez had some sort of a fight

163
00:16:43,597 --> 00:16:46,017
and Gomez feels
incredibly guilty about it.

164
00:16:46,183 --> 00:16:48,023
He'll tell you anything. Just ask.

165
00:16:48,310 --> 00:16:51,730
- It's foolproof.
- It had better be. Now, get out.

166
00:16:53,190 --> 00:16:54,320
It's gonna be great.

167
00:16:54,483 --> 00:16:57,323
You're gonna get back
all the money I owe you and more.

168
00:16:57,486 --> 00:16:58,736
You'll see. Really.

169
00:17:01,114 --> 00:17:04,744
This is it, Mother.
The one we've been waiting for.

170
00:17:04,910 --> 00:17:09,250
No more loan sharking,
no more storefront scams.

171
00:17:09,414 --> 00:17:11,674
I get the gold, and we're gone.

172
00:17:11,833 --> 00:17:15,093
And Tully takes the rap.
Gordon, it's brilliant.

173
00:17:15,254 --> 00:17:16,924
No, not Gordon!

174
00:17:17,339 --> 00:17:19,879
- Of course not.
- Fester.

175
00:17:27,683 --> 00:17:30,353
Big night for you guys, eh, small fry?

176
00:17:32,271 --> 00:17:33,941
Hello, sweetheart.

177
00:17:34,856 --> 00:17:36,226
Could you?

178
00:17:41,405 --> 00:17:43,905
Oh, thank God.

179
00:17:44,408 --> 00:17:46,408
Welcome, honored guests.

180
00:17:48,245 --> 00:17:49,535
Entrails?

181
00:18:04,344 --> 00:18:08,314
Sing, O spirits, hearken all souls.

182
00:18:09,141 --> 00:18:10,521
Every year on this date,

183
00:18:10,684 --> 00:18:13,604
we offer a clarion call
to Fester Addams.

184
00:18:13,770 --> 00:18:14,940
Stop it.

185
00:18:15,397 --> 00:18:16,647
Pugsley.

186
00:18:21,486 --> 00:18:22,606
Kids.

187
00:18:23,572 --> 00:18:25,782
From generation to generation,

188
00:18:26,616 --> 00:18:28,656
our beacon to the beyond.

189
00:18:30,579 --> 00:18:33,329
All close eyes and join hands.

190
00:18:39,921 --> 00:18:41,301
What a grip!

191
00:18:42,591 --> 00:18:43,801
My hand!

192
00:18:45,093 --> 00:18:47,803
My hand! She's got my hand!

193
00:18:56,730 --> 00:18:58,940
- Excuse me.
- Okay, pumpkin, sit down.

194
00:18:59,107 --> 00:19:02,187
- Join the fun.
- Mama, you should know better.

195
00:19:03,111 --> 00:19:05,151
Thing, you're a handful.

196
00:19:05,697 --> 00:19:07,067
Wednesday.

197
00:19:07,741 --> 00:19:10,411
Let us ransom you
from the power of the grave.

198
00:19:10,577 --> 00:19:13,327
Tonight, O Death, let us be your plague.

199
00:19:13,914 --> 00:19:15,214
Mama.

200
00:19:15,374 --> 00:19:17,214
Fester Addams,

201
00:19:24,424 --> 00:19:26,474
I feel that he's near.

202
00:19:29,137 --> 00:19:32,387
Fester Addams, gather your strength

203
00:19:33,308 --> 00:19:35,728
and knock three times.

204
00:19:40,315 --> 00:19:41,685
Did you hear that?

205
00:19:42,275 --> 00:19:44,185
- Ask again, Mama, quickly.
- By all means.

206
00:19:44,361 --> 00:19:45,531
Ask. Ask.

207
00:19:45,695 --> 00:19:50,905
Fester Addams,
I demand that you knock again!

208
00:20:03,422 --> 00:20:05,052
He's at the door!

209
00:20:21,022 --> 00:20:22,732
- Could it be?
- Is it him?

210
00:20:22,899 --> 00:20:25,029
- Is it possible?
- Oh, my God.

211
00:20:28,071 --> 00:20:30,741
- Fester.
- Gomez.

212
00:20:49,134 --> 00:20:52,394
Good evening. I am Dr. Pinder-Schloss.

213
00:20:56,725 --> 00:21:00,685
He was found in Miami,
tangled in a tuna net.

214
00:21:00,854 --> 00:21:05,074
It was just last month
during the Hurricane Helga.

215
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:08,360
The sky, it was black like pitch.

216
00:21:08,528 --> 00:21:12,738
The waves, they were walls of doom.
Can you imagine?

217
00:21:12,908 --> 00:21:16,238
They drag him from the ocean,
from the very jaws of oblivion.

218
00:21:16,411 --> 00:21:21,421
I'm telling you.
There were tests, so many tests!

219
00:21:21,625 --> 00:21:25,455
A complete psychological profile.

220
00:21:25,795 --> 00:21:26,915
At long last,

221
00:21:27,088 --> 00:21:29,628
the Florida Department
of the Fish and the Game,

222
00:21:29,799 --> 00:21:33,429
they say, "Lo and behold,
oh, my, oh, my, oh, my",

223
00:21:33,595 --> 00:21:35,965
"go tell it on the mountains,"

224
00:21:36,806 --> 00:21:38,556
"he is your brother."

225
00:21:40,894 --> 00:21:44,524
Boom! They give him to me
at Human Services,

226
00:21:44,689 --> 00:21:48,439
and I am bringing him,
after all these years,

227
00:21:48,735 --> 00:21:51,235
after who knows what heartache,

228
00:21:51,404 --> 00:21:53,744
after the naked and the dead,

229
00:21:53,907 --> 00:21:56,907
I am bringing him home to you!

230
00:21:57,536 --> 00:21:59,246
- That's preposterous.
- Margaret...

231
00:21:59,412 --> 00:22:01,572
Isn't that the most ridiculous thing
you've ever heard?

232
00:22:01,665 --> 00:22:03,865
- Possibly...
- It certainly is.

233
00:22:06,753 --> 00:22:08,963
- Now you're back.
- Yes, back.

234
00:22:09,130 --> 00:22:12,170
Back to share your joys, your sorrows.

235
00:22:12,342 --> 00:22:15,512
- Hey, everything.
- Well, I just don't know.

236
00:22:15,679 --> 00:22:17,759
Honey, how does this work, again?

237
00:22:17,931 --> 00:22:20,061
An infant would understand.

238
00:22:23,019 --> 00:22:26,479
Fester Addams, home at long last.

239
00:22:26,856 --> 00:22:30,476
Well, at least for a week.

240
00:22:30,652 --> 00:22:33,862
- A week?
- Don't be ridiculous. You're home.

241
00:22:34,030 --> 00:22:35,740
Sorry, but I have to get back.

242
00:22:35,907 --> 00:22:39,487
I've got a lot of things cooking
in the Bermuda Triangle.

243
00:22:39,661 --> 00:22:41,001
Oh, Gomez.

244
00:22:41,663 --> 00:22:44,503
- The Bermuda Triangle.
- Devil's Island.

245
00:22:44,666 --> 00:22:46,666
The Black Hole of Calcutta.

246
00:22:46,835 --> 00:22:49,835
- Excuse us.
- Second honeymoon.

247
00:22:51,256 --> 00:22:54,626
Dr. Pinder-Schloss,
will you be staying with us, too?

248
00:22:55,093 --> 00:22:57,263
No, no. I must be going.

249
00:22:57,429 --> 00:23:01,809
But I will be back, you can bet,
to be checking on Fester's adjustment.

250
00:23:03,226 --> 00:23:04,226
Cool.

251
00:23:04,394 --> 00:23:06,854
Nobody gets out of
the Bermuda Triangle.

252
00:23:07,022 --> 00:23:08,902
Not even for a vacation.

253
00:23:09,065 --> 00:23:10,565
Everyone knows that.

254
00:23:10,734 --> 00:23:14,494
Oh, my little bundle.
So much you don't understand.

255
00:23:14,654 --> 00:23:18,414
The human spirit,
it is a hard thing to kill.

256
00:23:19,326 --> 00:23:21,536
Even with a chain saw.

257
00:23:30,420 --> 00:23:33,260
Unpacking? Let me.

258
00:23:33,923 --> 00:23:36,053
It's all right. I can do it.

259
00:23:37,260 --> 00:23:38,590
Crowbar.

260
00:23:43,016 --> 00:23:44,216
Dynamite.

261
00:23:51,358 --> 00:23:52,688
Cyanide.

262
00:23:55,737 --> 00:23:58,907
Fester, as if we'd run out.

263
00:24:03,286 --> 00:24:04,656
Good night.

264
00:24:36,611 --> 00:24:38,281
Nosy little brat.

265
00:25:40,258 --> 00:25:41,718
Who's there?

266
00:26:17,587 --> 00:26:20,087
My own dear brother.

267
00:26:22,133 --> 00:26:25,723
- I've got goose bumps.
- I know.

268
00:26:27,222 --> 00:26:31,562
Screams in the night,
it can only mean one thing.

269
00:26:33,603 --> 00:26:34,943
He's home.

270
00:26:37,440 --> 00:26:39,900
Please! Please!

271
00:26:40,068 --> 00:26:42,568
Leave me alone!

272
00:27:09,639 --> 00:27:10,969
Breakfast?

273
00:27:12,600 --> 00:27:15,600
Damn, it's good to have you back.
Let's go.

274
00:27:18,648 --> 00:27:20,268
Two out of three?

275
00:27:25,405 --> 00:27:27,235
Home cooking!

276
00:27:27,407 --> 00:27:30,237
There's nothing like it in the world.

277
00:27:30,702 --> 00:27:32,492
May I have the salt?

278
00:27:34,539 --> 00:27:36,159
What do we say?

279
00:27:37,500 --> 00:27:38,580
Now.

280
00:27:48,511 --> 00:27:52,601
- What is this?
- Mama's spécialité de la Maison.

281
00:27:52,932 --> 00:27:54,642
Oh, Tish.

282
00:27:57,395 --> 00:27:59,185
Start with the eyes.

283
00:28:01,733 --> 00:28:03,573
Did you sleep well?

284
00:28:05,028 --> 00:28:07,238
- Like the dead.
- Really?

285
00:28:07,405 --> 00:28:09,085
Who would have thought
the Bermuda Triangle

286
00:28:09,198 --> 00:28:10,658
could change a man so much?

287
00:28:10,825 --> 00:28:14,905
You used to toss and turn all night.
We had to chain you to the bedpost.

288
00:28:15,079 --> 00:28:16,869
Doesn't make sense.

289
00:28:18,249 --> 00:28:22,879
The Bermuda Triangle is a very strange
and mysterious place.

290
00:28:23,504 --> 00:28:26,724
You'd be surprised
at all the things you don't know.

291
00:28:28,217 --> 00:28:29,887
She certainly would.

292
00:28:30,053 --> 00:28:32,473
Wednesday adores
the Bermuda Triangle.

293
00:28:32,639 --> 00:28:35,809
She studies it.
Death at sea, she's hooked.

294
00:28:36,017 --> 00:28:37,637
Ask me anything.

295
00:28:41,356 --> 00:28:44,396
Being in my old room
sure brings back memories.

296
00:28:45,735 --> 00:28:49,065
- Remember Camp Custer?
- For preteen offenders.

297
00:28:58,581 --> 00:29:00,581
Aren't memories precious?

298
00:29:01,084 --> 00:29:04,594
Today I'd like to wander
through the house, remembering.

299
00:29:04,754 --> 00:29:06,964
No, no. Sorry, old man.
No wandering today.

300
00:29:07,131 --> 00:29:09,551
Today we're going straight to the vault.

301
00:29:19,727 --> 00:29:22,267
Bravo, Pugsley!

302
00:29:28,403 --> 00:29:29,743
- "Greed"!
- "Greed"!

303
00:29:38,287 --> 00:29:40,747
I feel like we're children again.

304
00:29:40,957 --> 00:29:42,497
Tag. You're it!

305
00:30:05,231 --> 00:30:07,481
Smell that air, Fester.

306
00:30:11,237 --> 00:30:12,607
Like a tomb.

307
00:30:19,787 --> 00:30:22,327
The sea, your second home.

308
00:30:23,624 --> 00:30:25,134
Ship ahoy.

309
00:30:40,767 --> 00:30:42,927
Do you think that's really Uncle Fester?

310
00:30:43,102 --> 00:30:46,102
Father says so,
but I think Mother isn't sure.

311
00:30:50,109 --> 00:30:51,399
Pugsley, sit in the chair.

312
00:30:51,569 --> 00:30:53,739
- Why?
- So we can play a game.

313
00:30:59,243 --> 00:31:00,583
What game?

314
00:31:01,871 --> 00:31:05,421
It's called, "Is There a God?"

315
00:31:30,233 --> 00:31:31,613
The vault!

316
00:31:33,069 --> 00:31:36,529
Two to the right, ten to the left.

317
00:31:36,697 --> 00:31:39,317
And then around to...

318
00:31:39,867 --> 00:31:40,947
Five.

319
00:31:41,869 --> 00:31:43,079
Eleven.

320
00:31:44,038 --> 00:31:47,038
Two, ten, eleven. Eyes, fingers, toes.

321
00:31:47,750 --> 00:31:49,250
So many years.

322
00:31:59,095 --> 00:32:01,555
- Welcome back.
- Thanks.

323
00:32:02,723 --> 00:32:04,723
Our secret place.

324
00:32:07,937 --> 00:32:10,727
If these walls could speak, eh, old man?

325
00:32:10,898 --> 00:32:14,898
- What would they say?
- You tell me.

326
00:32:15,736 --> 00:32:17,066
You first.

327
00:32:18,072 --> 00:32:19,572
Senior partner.

328
00:32:20,366 --> 00:32:21,906
Junior spaceman.

329
00:32:24,036 --> 00:32:25,786
First a brandy. Do the honors.

330
00:32:25,955 --> 00:32:28,075
I've got a real treat in store.

331
00:32:28,249 --> 00:32:30,829
Where is it, you ridiculous imbecile?

332
00:33:16,047 --> 00:33:17,837
Show time!

333
00:33:47,703 --> 00:33:50,123
There, the debutante ball.

334
00:33:51,624 --> 00:33:53,794
Remember that fateful night?

335
00:33:54,752 --> 00:33:56,092
Of course.

336
00:34:01,467 --> 00:34:02,877
Your first cigar.

337
00:34:03,052 --> 00:34:06,392
What? Come on, old man.
I've smoked since I was five.

338
00:34:06,555 --> 00:34:08,215
Mother insisted.

339
00:34:10,393 --> 00:34:13,193
Flora and Fauna.

340
00:34:13,479 --> 00:34:15,899
Quite the pair, eh, Gomez?

341
00:34:16,232 --> 00:34:17,982
Can you ever forgive me?

342
00:34:19,860 --> 00:34:20,900
What?

343
00:34:21,362 --> 00:34:23,322
I didn't love them,

344
00:34:23,489 --> 00:34:26,739
yet I wooed them both
out of foolish pride.

345
00:34:27,702 --> 00:34:30,372
You were so dashing,
you could have any woman you wanted,

346
00:34:30,538 --> 00:34:32,038
dead or alive.

347
00:34:32,665 --> 00:34:34,115
I was jealous.

348
00:34:34,292 --> 00:34:36,502
Insanely jealous.

349
00:34:36,669 --> 00:34:38,379
I admit that now.

350
00:34:41,465 --> 00:34:44,215
But I did not mean to drive you off,

351
00:34:44,385 --> 00:34:46,545
not to the Bermuda Triangle.

352
00:34:47,054 --> 00:34:48,894
Water under the bridge.

353
00:34:49,390 --> 00:34:51,520
Forgiven. Forgotten.

354
00:34:59,233 --> 00:35:01,073
Come on. Say it.

355
00:35:01,902 --> 00:35:04,612
- Say the secret password.
- The password?

356
00:35:05,406 --> 00:35:07,566
Come on. Stop fooling. You remember.

357
00:35:07,742 --> 00:35:10,662
Please. I'm choking. Please.

358
00:35:10,828 --> 00:35:13,538
You forgot our secret password?

359
00:35:13,706 --> 00:35:16,076
The word we used 100 times a day?

360
00:35:16,250 --> 00:35:18,380
Our special private name
for each other?

361
00:35:18,544 --> 00:35:20,714
That was a long time ago
when we were children.

362
00:35:20,880 --> 00:35:22,210
You almost killed me,

363
00:35:22,381 --> 00:35:26,221
you demented freak.

364
00:35:26,385 --> 00:35:29,715
Poor devil, what did they do to you
in that Bermuda Triangle?

365
00:35:29,889 --> 00:35:32,389
But if he's not Uncle Fester,
then who is he?

366
00:35:32,558 --> 00:35:34,058
Somebody else.

367
00:35:37,146 --> 00:35:38,396
It has to warm up.

368
00:35:38,564 --> 00:35:41,654
- Why?
- So it can kill you.

369
00:35:42,276 --> 00:35:43,776
I knew that.

370
00:35:44,612 --> 00:35:48,282
- Children, what are you doing?
- I'm going to electrocute him.

371
00:35:48,449 --> 00:35:50,579
But we're late for the charity auction.

372
00:35:50,743 --> 00:35:53,293
- But, Mother...
- I said no.

373
00:35:53,913 --> 00:35:55,123
Please?

374
00:35:56,082 --> 00:35:57,582
Oh, all right.

375
00:36:07,426 --> 00:36:08,836
This magnificent piece

376
00:36:09,428 --> 00:36:13,008
is encrusted with rubies
and 15 emerald chips.

377
00:36:13,349 --> 00:36:18,599
It was donated
by Morticia and Gomez Addams.

378
00:36:18,854 --> 00:36:21,364
Remember, this year,
over half our proceeds

379
00:36:21,524 --> 00:36:24,654
will benefit the elderly
and the mentally disabled.

380
00:36:25,319 --> 00:36:28,409
I'll open the bidding at $5,000.

381
00:36:28,572 --> 00:36:31,202
Five... Not good enough.

382
00:36:31,367 --> 00:36:33,577
- $20,000.
- What are they doing?

383
00:36:33,744 --> 00:36:36,414
- I have 20.
- Twenty-five.

384
00:36:37,123 --> 00:36:38,463
Twenty-five.

385
00:36:38,624 --> 00:36:39,874
Thirty.

386
00:36:41,001 --> 00:36:42,421
Thirty-five!

387
00:36:44,463 --> 00:36:48,383
- Fifty.
- I have $50,000.

388
00:36:48,551 --> 00:36:49,931
Your turn, my ecstasy.

389
00:36:50,094 --> 00:36:53,684
$50,000, going once.
$50,000, going twice.

390
00:36:55,516 --> 00:36:59,936
Sold to Morticia Addams for $50,000.

391
00:37:11,407 --> 00:37:13,367
Isn't it too enchanting?

392
00:37:13,534 --> 00:37:15,414
How do you take it off?

393
00:37:18,205 --> 00:37:20,165
There's a trick to it,

394
00:37:22,543 --> 00:37:23,923
of course.

395
00:37:34,263 --> 00:37:37,063
"How do you take it off?" That's absurd.

396
00:37:37,391 --> 00:37:40,891
That finger trap was a party favor
at his 10th birthday!

397
00:37:45,691 --> 00:37:46,941
Oh, no.

398
00:37:47,526 --> 00:37:49,236
Father's playing with his trains.

399
00:37:50,905 --> 00:37:53,195
He wore that finger trap for two years!

400
00:37:53,365 --> 00:37:55,365
Mother had to teach him
to eat with his feet.

401
00:37:55,534 --> 00:37:58,164
And the combination and the password

402
00:37:58,329 --> 00:38:00,909
and my cigar and he slept so well!

403
00:38:04,627 --> 00:38:06,037
He's using the diesel.

404
00:38:17,640 --> 00:38:18,720
The covered bridge.

405
00:38:22,102 --> 00:38:23,312
Dead man's curve.

406
00:39:17,157 --> 00:39:19,827
It's all about Uncle Fester, isn't it?

407
00:39:29,878 --> 00:39:32,628
Spirits above me, give me a sign.

408
00:39:33,173 --> 00:39:35,883
Shall I be joyous or shall I be damned?

409
00:39:51,734 --> 00:39:53,404
Sleepless night?

410
00:39:56,322 --> 00:39:58,112
Walk with me, Fester.

411
00:40:04,204 --> 00:40:05,714
Aunt LaBorgia.

412
00:40:06,165 --> 00:40:08,365
Executed by a firing squad.

413
00:40:09,877 --> 00:40:11,377
Cousin Fledge.

414
00:40:11,879 --> 00:40:14,959
Torn limb from limb by four wild horses.

415
00:40:16,550 --> 00:40:18,840
Darling Uncle Eimar.

416
00:40:21,722 --> 00:40:23,182
Buried alive.

417
00:40:24,516 --> 00:40:27,556
Psychopaths, fiends,

418
00:40:27,728 --> 00:40:29,398
mad-dog killers.

419
00:40:30,064 --> 00:40:32,904
Brutes, Fester. Pioneers.

420
00:40:33,484 --> 00:40:35,074
Lest we forget.

421
00:40:36,362 --> 00:40:38,202
Your beloved Muerto.

422
00:40:39,990 --> 00:40:43,200
After you left,
he was simply a different vulture.

423
00:40:44,953 --> 00:40:46,703
He wouldn't circle.

424
00:40:47,706 --> 00:40:49,366
He wouldn't peck.

425
00:40:50,834 --> 00:40:53,544
That's how much
you mean to this family.

426
00:41:00,678 --> 00:41:02,718
Mother and Father Addams.

427
00:41:04,056 --> 00:41:07,426
How I wish the children
could have known them better.

428
00:41:08,227 --> 00:41:10,557
But tell that to an angry mob.

429
00:41:13,941 --> 00:41:18,741
And our credo,
"Sic gorgiamus allos subjectatos nunc."

430
00:41:19,530 --> 00:41:22,870
We gladly feast
on those who would subdue us.

431
00:41:23,784 --> 00:41:25,704
Not just pretty words.

432
00:41:29,248 --> 00:41:33,418
As an Addams,
you understand completely, don't you?

433
00:41:35,963 --> 00:41:39,053
As an Addams, yes, I do.

434
00:41:42,636 --> 00:41:44,386
Good night, Fester.

435
00:41:46,932 --> 00:41:48,472
Rest in peace.

436
00:41:57,818 --> 00:41:59,938
They're on to me, Mother.
I'm almost sure.

437
00:42:00,487 --> 00:42:02,317
Of course I tried.
I still can't find it.

438
00:42:02,489 --> 00:42:03,609
You've got to get over here.

439
00:42:03,657 --> 00:42:05,947
Arsenic, cyanide. Cyanide.
Arsenic, arsenic.

440
00:42:06,452 --> 00:42:07,992
Don't say that.

441
00:42:09,288 --> 00:42:10,788
You know I do.

442
00:42:13,000 --> 00:42:16,920
His trains are everywhere.
The children are beside themselves.

443
00:42:17,588 --> 00:42:19,588
Is that for your brother?

444
00:42:19,923 --> 00:42:21,553
I don't think so.

445
00:42:29,558 --> 00:42:31,178
This can't go on.

446
00:42:31,351 --> 00:42:33,851
How can I help him? Tell me, Mama.

447
00:42:35,397 --> 00:42:37,817
"Troubled husbands."

448
00:42:37,983 --> 00:42:39,693
- "Adultery"?
- Oh, no.

449
00:42:40,694 --> 00:42:43,574
- "Financial, money troubles"?
- No.

450
00:42:44,782 --> 00:42:48,242
- "Turned into toad or reptile."
- Is there an index?

451
00:42:50,245 --> 00:42:53,155
They know I'm a fraud, the whole bunch.

452
00:42:53,791 --> 00:42:55,171
It's not going to work.

453
00:42:55,334 --> 00:42:58,674
Who knows?
Gomez, that overheated moron?

454
00:42:59,129 --> 00:43:01,709
He's no moron. He's Fester's brother.

455
00:43:01,882 --> 00:43:03,422
They had some awful fight years ago.

456
00:43:03,592 --> 00:43:05,682
He's suspicious,
they all are, I can tell.

457
00:43:05,844 --> 00:43:08,054
Really? Well,
thank God I came over here.

458
00:43:08,222 --> 00:43:12,732
I will counsel the troubled family,
ease their distress.

459
00:43:12,893 --> 00:43:15,523
It's my calling. Remember, Gordon?

460
00:43:15,687 --> 00:43:18,687
- What?
- I'm a doctor.

461
00:43:21,485 --> 00:43:25,025
Why don't you speak to Fester, darling?
He's right outside the door.

462
00:43:25,197 --> 00:43:28,317
I would speak with Fester
if that were Fester.

463
00:43:28,534 --> 00:43:31,704
But that is not. That's an impostor!

464
00:43:31,870 --> 00:43:34,330
An impostore!

465
00:43:34,540 --> 00:43:37,210
A charlatan! A sham!

466
00:43:37,543 --> 00:43:39,043
A counterfeit.

467
00:43:46,552 --> 00:43:49,892
O, villain, villain,
smiling, damned villain!

468
00:43:50,055 --> 00:43:52,215
Who calls me a villain?
Breaks my pate across?

469
00:43:52,391 --> 00:43:53,701
- Bloodshed.
- Plucks off my beard,

470
00:43:53,725 --> 00:43:57,515
- and blows it in my face?
- If I must strike you dead, I will.

471
00:44:07,614 --> 00:44:08,664
No!

472
00:44:08,991 --> 00:44:12,241
No, no, no, no, no, no!

473
00:44:13,954 --> 00:44:15,714
Give me that sword.

474
00:44:16,623 --> 00:44:18,793
Haven't you ever slaughtered anyone?

475
00:44:18,959 --> 00:44:21,669
- He's only a child.
- No excuse.

476
00:44:22,462 --> 00:44:25,462
Aim for a major artery. The jugular.

477
00:44:25,632 --> 00:44:28,802
A faker! A phony!

478
00:44:28,969 --> 00:44:30,679
An utter fraud!

479
00:44:31,096 --> 00:44:35,136
- A base, deceitful...
- Mr. Addams!

480
00:44:36,435 --> 00:44:39,645
I believe I am understanding.
I can help, yes?

481
00:44:40,272 --> 00:44:43,612
The theory of displacement.

482
00:44:44,276 --> 00:44:45,936
Is this familiar?

483
00:44:46,528 --> 00:44:47,778
No. Tish?

484
00:44:47,946 --> 00:44:50,446
Oh, it is too exciting.

485
00:44:50,824 --> 00:44:52,494
I will explain.

486
00:44:52,784 --> 00:44:54,744
Is it unpleasant?

487
00:44:55,454 --> 00:44:56,664
Deeply.

488
00:44:58,790 --> 00:45:02,880
Your very own brother,
you drive him away.

489
00:45:03,045 --> 00:45:04,835
"Go. Off with you."

490
00:45:05,213 --> 00:45:09,053
But then you are feeling
the little black monster.

491
00:45:09,217 --> 00:45:11,717
- Pugsley.
- Guilt. Yes?

492
00:45:12,387 --> 00:45:15,467
Your brother returns, you feel guilty,

493
00:45:15,641 --> 00:45:18,231
- you displace.
- I do?

494
00:45:18,560 --> 00:45:22,270
The feelings in your brain cells,
they bubble and collide.

495
00:45:22,981 --> 00:45:25,481
You suspect things.

496
00:45:25,651 --> 00:45:28,361
You love him, but you resent him.

497
00:45:28,862 --> 00:45:30,992
Love, hate. Hate, love.

498
00:45:32,032 --> 00:45:33,702
Like for Mama. No?

499
00:45:34,201 --> 00:45:37,121
But I didn't hate my mother,
it was an accident.

500
00:45:37,287 --> 00:45:41,707
It's a very common psychosis,
I'm seeing it every day.

501
00:45:42,000 --> 00:45:43,500
Lucky doctor.

502
00:45:44,044 --> 00:45:47,384
Displacement. How bizarre.

503
00:45:47,547 --> 00:45:50,377
And here I thought
Fester was the problem.

504
00:45:51,051 --> 00:45:52,391
- He's sullen.
- He's furtive.

505
00:45:52,552 --> 00:45:53,682
- Backstabbing.
- He sulks.

506
00:45:53,845 --> 00:45:55,285
- I suspect him.
- You're unbalanced.

507
00:45:55,347 --> 00:45:58,887
And I hate him. By God, you're right!

508
00:45:59,393 --> 00:46:01,063
He is Fester!

509
00:46:01,436 --> 00:46:03,686
Thank you, Dr. Pinder-Schloss.

510
00:46:04,231 --> 00:46:05,861
I do what I can.

511
00:46:06,024 --> 00:46:08,784
You see, children,
there's lots to learn.

512
00:46:12,906 --> 00:46:14,276
"Gangrene."

513
00:46:16,243 --> 00:46:18,373
Uncle Fester,
how do you know so much?

514
00:46:18,537 --> 00:46:21,077
I've been around. I pick things up.

515
00:46:21,415 --> 00:46:23,365
In the Bermuda Triangle?

516
00:46:25,293 --> 00:46:27,553
Look, children, a new chapter.

517
00:46:28,046 --> 00:46:30,376
- "Scabs."
- "Scabs."

518
00:46:37,472 --> 00:46:40,732
Three parts dynamite
with a nitroglycerin cap.

519
00:46:40,934 --> 00:46:44,694
It's perfect for small holes,
carports and tool sheds.

520
00:46:51,528 --> 00:46:52,738
Mother.

521
00:46:53,572 --> 00:46:56,032
Everyone will be
at the children's play tonight, correct?

522
00:46:56,199 --> 00:46:58,199
Oh, yes. I've been working with them.

523
00:46:58,368 --> 00:47:00,868
- It's going to be fun.
- Fun?

524
00:47:02,706 --> 00:47:05,286
Is that what we're here for? Fun?

525
00:47:06,126 --> 00:47:08,746
Darling, forgive me.
You see what they've driven me to?

526
00:47:08,920 --> 00:47:12,300
I've raised a hand to my child,
my reason for living.

527
00:47:14,176 --> 00:47:17,886
- You can't go to the play.
- But the kids...

528
00:47:18,055 --> 00:47:20,555
The house will be deserted.
The vault will be ours.

529
00:47:20,724 --> 00:47:22,104
But, Mother...

530
00:47:23,560 --> 00:47:25,640
Can you hear it, my treasure?

531
00:47:25,812 --> 00:47:28,402
My heartbeat. It beats only for you.

532
00:47:28,565 --> 00:47:31,315
Listen closely.
It says, "Gordon, I love you",

533
00:47:31,485 --> 00:47:33,565
"Gordon, the vault."

534
00:47:34,696 --> 00:47:36,196
I do hear it.

535
00:47:36,531 --> 00:47:40,491
Soon we'll have the money
and we'll be far from here.

536
00:47:40,911 --> 00:47:44,001
Loving mother, grateful son.

537
00:47:44,664 --> 00:47:45,794
Understood?

538
00:47:51,922 --> 00:47:54,012
There you are, at last.

539
00:47:55,217 --> 00:47:57,927
What a fool I was to doubt you.

540
00:47:58,095 --> 00:48:00,845
Dr. Pinder-Schloss
explained everything.

541
00:48:01,014 --> 00:48:03,354
What a lovely woman. So chilly.

542
00:48:03,767 --> 00:48:06,887
Displacement. It's a common psychosis.

543
00:48:07,062 --> 00:48:09,152
- Isn't that grand?
- Is it?

544
00:48:10,190 --> 00:48:11,900
Look at it, Fester.

545
00:48:12,067 --> 00:48:16,397
The primeval ooze.
Quicksand, fumes, toxic waste.

546
00:48:16,571 --> 00:48:20,701
It's all ours, Fester.
You belong here, old man.

547
00:48:21,034 --> 00:48:23,834
- Stay.
- You don't know what you're asking.

548
00:48:24,579 --> 00:48:28,039
You have a beautiful wife,
wonderful children,

549
00:48:28,875 --> 00:48:30,325
a wasteland.

550
00:48:31,419 --> 00:48:32,999
I'm in the way.

551
00:48:33,713 --> 00:48:34,883
In the way?

552
00:48:35,715 --> 00:48:38,375
- My brother?
- Gomez, take care!

553
00:48:40,220 --> 00:48:43,060
For you, life is all fun and games.

554
00:48:43,890 --> 00:48:46,980
A dance in a graveyard. Stench. Decay.

555
00:48:47,519 --> 00:48:51,019
- But things change.
- Precisely. You're back.

556
00:48:52,065 --> 00:48:54,895
All those years apart, Fester.

557
00:48:55,527 --> 00:48:57,397
We can't do that again.

558
00:49:00,198 --> 00:49:01,778
You're home.

559
00:49:25,599 --> 00:49:26,769
Fore!

560
00:49:31,229 --> 00:49:33,109
Damn you, Addams!

561
00:49:39,404 --> 00:49:40,704
Uncle Fester?

562
00:49:40,864 --> 00:49:43,624
Come on, Uncle Fester.
Come to the play.

563
00:49:44,367 --> 00:49:46,287
I said I was busy.

564
00:49:46,620 --> 00:49:50,960
But you said you'd help us,
with the Shakespeare and the pus.

565
00:49:51,124 --> 00:49:52,794
I changed my mind.

566
00:50:07,599 --> 00:50:10,269
Mrs. Addams,
can I see you for a moment?

567
00:50:11,436 --> 00:50:13,896
I'm Susan Firkins.
I'm Wednesday's teacher.

568
00:50:14,064 --> 00:50:15,564
Oh, of course, Miss Firkins.

569
00:50:15,732 --> 00:50:18,322
Wednesday's told us
so much about you.

570
00:50:26,952 --> 00:50:31,662
Wednesday is an excellent student,
but, frankly, I'm concerned.

571
00:50:31,831 --> 00:50:34,211
You see,
this is our class bulletin board.

572
00:50:34,376 --> 00:50:38,916
This month, our theme is our heroes,
people we love and admire.

573
00:50:39,381 --> 00:50:42,301
You see, Susan Ringo
has chosen the President.

574
00:50:42,467 --> 00:50:43,967
Isn't that sweet?

575
00:50:44,469 --> 00:50:47,639
And Harmony Feld
has picked Jane Pauley.

576
00:50:49,599 --> 00:50:51,889
Have you spoken to her parents?

577
00:50:52,644 --> 00:50:56,024
But Wednesday brought in this picture,

578
00:50:56,189 --> 00:50:58,109
Calpurnia Addams.

579
00:50:58,566 --> 00:51:01,436
Wednesday's great-aunt Calpurnia.

580
00:51:01,611 --> 00:51:04,361
She was burned as a witch in 1706.

581
00:51:04,698 --> 00:51:07,618
They say she danced naked
in the town square

582
00:51:07,784 --> 00:51:09,794
and enslaved a minister.

583
00:51:10,537 --> 00:51:12,707
- Really?
- Oh, yes.

584
00:51:13,373 --> 00:51:17,793
But don't worry.
We've told Wednesday, college first.

585
00:51:19,004 --> 00:51:22,054
Isn't he adorable?

586
00:51:22,674 --> 00:51:25,844
- I made this myself.
- It's charming.

587
00:51:26,011 --> 00:51:27,761
What is he, a lizard?

588
00:51:28,263 --> 00:51:29,513
An elf.

589
00:51:30,640 --> 00:51:32,310
Look at you.

590
00:51:38,815 --> 00:51:40,645
That's better.

591
00:51:41,026 --> 00:51:43,686
You are too precious for words.

592
00:51:43,862 --> 00:51:46,452
Why, I could just eat you alive.

593
00:51:46,865 --> 00:51:49,025
Oh, no, Margaret. Too young.

594
00:52:20,607 --> 00:52:23,857
Wednesday. Pugsley.
I changed my mind.

595
00:52:24,736 --> 00:52:26,236
Uncle Fester.

596
00:52:32,869 --> 00:52:34,869
Gordon? Gordon?

597
00:52:35,955 --> 00:52:37,365
It's Mother.

598
00:52:40,543 --> 00:52:42,383
Damn it, where is he?

599
00:52:43,254 --> 00:52:45,594
I never should have used him.

600
00:52:56,017 --> 00:52:58,727
I knew you couldn't stay away, old man.

601
00:53:18,331 --> 00:53:19,581
Damn it.

602
00:53:20,917 --> 00:53:23,287
Gordon! Gordon!

603
00:53:23,461 --> 00:53:24,961
Are you there?

604
00:53:26,548 --> 00:53:27,838
Gordon.

605
00:53:32,345 --> 00:53:34,845
My goodness! Say! Look!
Would somebody come here!

606
00:53:35,014 --> 00:53:36,814
Oh, my! Oh, good...

607
00:53:37,559 --> 00:53:38,979
Oh, my!

608
00:53:40,353 --> 00:53:42,233
How all occasions
do inform against me,

609
00:53:42,397 --> 00:53:44,107
And spur my dull revenge!

610
00:53:44,274 --> 00:53:45,484
O, from this time forth,

611
00:53:45,650 --> 00:53:47,570
My thoughts be bloody,
or nothing worth!

612
00:53:47,735 --> 00:53:50,235
If I must strike you dead, I will.

613
00:53:53,491 --> 00:53:54,661
A hit,

614
00:53:55,243 --> 00:53:57,703
a very palpable hit.

615
00:54:08,381 --> 00:54:10,171
O proud death,

616
00:54:10,341 --> 00:54:13,221
What feast is toward
in thine eternal cell?

617
00:54:15,513 --> 00:54:18,853
Sweet oblivion, open your arms!

618
00:54:36,409 --> 00:54:37,739
Bravo!

619
00:54:39,412 --> 00:54:41,872
- Bravo!
- Bravo!

620
00:54:42,415 --> 00:54:49,705
Bravo!

621
00:54:49,923 --> 00:54:52,843
There were sailors, pirates

622
00:54:53,676 --> 00:54:57,346
and a plane full of tourists
from Miami Beach,

623
00:54:58,056 --> 00:55:00,136
all lost in the Triangle.

624
00:55:00,683 --> 00:55:03,693
Uncle Fester,
will you take me there someday?

625
00:55:03,937 --> 00:55:05,477
It's a promise.

626
00:55:06,397 --> 00:55:08,017
- Good night, Wednesday.
- Good night.

627
00:55:08,191 --> 00:55:09,861
You were terrific.

628
00:55:12,153 --> 00:55:13,613
Uncle Fester?

629
00:55:35,468 --> 00:55:37,258
A theatrical triumph.

630
00:55:38,054 --> 00:55:39,724
It's like a dream.

631
00:55:40,139 --> 00:55:43,479
When we first met,
it was an evening much like this.

632
00:55:44,102 --> 00:55:45,732
Magic in the air.

633
00:55:46,813 --> 00:55:47,983
A boy.

634
00:55:48,773 --> 00:55:49,983
A girl.

635
00:55:50,733 --> 00:55:52,233
An open grave.

636
00:55:52,986 --> 00:55:54,946
It was my first funeral.

637
00:55:55,738 --> 00:55:57,818
You were so beautiful.

638
00:55:58,616 --> 00:56:00,446
Pale and mysterious.

639
00:56:01,494 --> 00:56:03,874
No one even looked at the corpse.

640
00:56:04,372 --> 00:56:06,332
Your cousin, Balthazar.

641
00:56:07,000 --> 00:56:09,000
You were still a suspect.

642
00:56:10,378 --> 00:56:14,008
I couldn't stop staring at you
all through the eulogy.

643
00:56:15,341 --> 00:56:18,801
Your eyes, your moustache,

644
00:56:20,179 --> 00:56:21,509
your laugh.

645
00:56:23,349 --> 00:56:25,019
You bewitched me.

646
00:56:26,436 --> 00:56:28,516
I proposed that very night.

647
00:56:29,522 --> 00:56:33,192
Just think,
someday we'll be buried here

648
00:56:33,818 --> 00:56:36,608
side by side, six feet under

649
00:56:36,988 --> 00:56:38,858
in matching coffins.

650
00:56:39,866 --> 00:56:42,026
Our lifeless bodies

651
00:56:42,201 --> 00:56:46,291
rotting together for all eternity.

652
00:56:48,666 --> 00:56:50,206
Cara Mia.

653
00:56:51,711 --> 00:56:53,341
Mon Sauvage.

654
00:57:24,202 --> 00:57:25,912
Hey, Bigfoot.

655
00:57:30,375 --> 00:57:32,575
Don't stare. Just get me out.

656
00:57:39,342 --> 00:57:40,342
Did you like the blood?

657
00:57:41,886 --> 00:57:44,506
- I was so proud.
- Weren't we all?

658
00:57:45,348 --> 00:57:47,598
Wednesday, play with your food.

659
00:57:55,566 --> 00:57:56,726
Mama.

660
00:57:56,901 --> 00:57:58,691
Who put this in here?

661
00:58:01,698 --> 00:58:04,238
- That's for company.
- Rascals.

662
00:58:05,159 --> 00:58:08,039
Doctor, you were so right.

663
00:58:08,204 --> 00:58:10,964
- What an evening.
- Fester fit right in.

664
00:58:11,124 --> 00:58:14,424
- The displacement is over.
- Well, isn't that nice.

665
00:58:14,627 --> 00:58:18,167
- Does he really have to go?
- Yes, he does.

666
00:58:18,339 --> 00:58:21,509
Well, if he insists upon leaving,

667
00:58:21,968 --> 00:58:24,178
we shall mark the occasion.

668
00:58:24,971 --> 00:58:26,141
Tish?

669
00:58:26,305 --> 00:58:30,885
- We've planned a farewell party.
- We've invited the entire clan.

670
00:58:31,352 --> 00:58:33,402
What a lovely gesture.

671
00:58:33,646 --> 00:58:35,356
We're a family again

672
00:58:35,523 --> 00:58:37,903
and we owe it all to you,
Dr. Pinder-Schloss.

673
00:58:38,067 --> 00:58:40,357
Please. Greta.

674
00:58:40,820 --> 00:58:41,900
Greta.

675
00:58:43,156 --> 00:58:45,316
Fester, walk me out.

676
00:58:49,912 --> 00:58:53,672
I'm fine, Mother.
I'm completely in control.

677
00:58:53,833 --> 00:58:56,173
They're not your family, Gordon. I am.

678
00:58:56,335 --> 00:58:58,085
They don't love you. I do.

679
00:58:58,254 --> 00:59:01,674
They're evil and corrupt and degraded.

680
00:59:01,841 --> 00:59:05,051
- I can give you that.
- I'm fine. Really.

681
00:59:05,428 --> 00:59:07,258
We'll see. Open up!

682
00:59:36,375 --> 00:59:37,665
A party?

683
00:59:38,503 --> 00:59:39,673
For me?

684
00:59:41,088 --> 00:59:42,168
Here?

685
00:59:49,680 --> 00:59:53,850
Tish, how long has it been
since we've waltzed?

686
00:59:54,769 --> 00:59:56,189
Oh, Gomez.

687
01:00:00,900 --> 01:00:02,070
Hours.

688
01:01:09,468 --> 01:01:10,888
It, old man!

689
01:01:13,431 --> 01:01:15,681
You're right. Far too long.

690
01:01:22,106 --> 01:01:24,936
- Don't let me out of your sight.
- Don't threaten me, Margaret.

691
01:01:25,109 --> 01:01:28,109
- These people are abnormal.
- Don't exaggerate.

692
01:01:34,660 --> 01:01:37,450
Oh, by all means!
They're clients, Margaret.

693
01:01:45,004 --> 01:01:47,424
- Wednesday?
- Yes, Mother?

694
01:01:47,590 --> 01:01:51,090
Would you run upstairs
and check on your uncle, please?

695
01:01:52,261 --> 01:01:55,311
Why, Lumpy Addams. Look at you.

696
01:01:56,182 --> 01:01:57,642
All grown up.

697
01:02:10,071 --> 01:02:11,531
Uncle Fester?

698
01:02:14,533 --> 01:02:16,533
- I understand.
- I hope so.

699
01:02:16,702 --> 01:02:17,992
And I'm counting on you.

700
01:02:18,162 --> 01:02:20,792
Don't let me down. Don't buckle.

701
01:02:20,957 --> 01:02:23,787
It's not gonna be easy.
There are people everywhere.

702
01:02:23,960 --> 01:02:26,670
You can do it if you just stop whining.

703
01:02:27,338 --> 01:02:29,838
Nobody likes that. It's unattractive.

704
01:02:30,007 --> 01:02:34,507
All right. Fine.
I will try and reach the vault tonight.

705
01:02:34,971 --> 01:02:38,391
But if I can't, well, then that's it.

706
01:02:39,517 --> 01:02:40,977
Okay, Mother?

707
01:02:41,310 --> 01:02:44,020
I knew it. You are a fake.

708
01:02:44,313 --> 01:02:46,563
Come here, my little one.

709
01:02:46,732 --> 01:02:48,532
- Wednesday!
- Get her!

710
01:03:34,155 --> 01:03:37,235
Flora and Fauna Amor.

711
01:03:38,492 --> 01:03:40,162
I cannot see.

712
01:03:40,536 --> 01:03:43,286
I am blinded by such beauty.

713
01:03:43,456 --> 01:03:44,536
Gomez Addams.

714
01:03:44,707 --> 01:03:46,417
- You terrible flirt.
- Always was.

715
01:03:46,584 --> 01:03:47,754
- At least with me.
- Copycat!

716
01:03:47,918 --> 01:03:51,298
- Tag-along!
- Why, Gomez, the Amor twins.

717
01:03:51,547 --> 01:03:53,967
- I've heard so much about you.
- Morticia...

718
01:03:54,133 --> 01:03:55,843
- You nabbed him.
- This darling man.

719
01:03:56,010 --> 01:03:57,680
- He was mine!
- He was mine!

720
01:03:57,845 --> 01:04:00,215
Flora, Fauna, how can I compete?

721
01:04:00,598 --> 01:04:02,808
You're twice the woman I am.

722
01:04:03,142 --> 01:04:05,692
Tully, the Amor twins.

723
01:04:06,020 --> 01:04:08,690
They're waiting for Fester. Amuse them.

724
01:04:11,150 --> 01:04:13,690
- Hello, Tully.
- Oh, my God.

725
01:04:19,950 --> 01:04:22,950
You mean you don't know?
It's too intriguing.

726
01:04:23,120 --> 01:04:26,500
Now that Fester's back,
he's king of the castle again, isn't he?

727
01:04:26,665 --> 01:04:29,075
Fester's the older brother,
so he gets it all.

728
01:04:29,251 --> 01:04:31,291
The house, the money, you name it.

729
01:04:31,462 --> 01:04:33,342
Fester's still single, isn't he?

730
01:04:33,506 --> 01:04:36,166
- Are you, Mr. Alford?
- Why, Fauna.

731
01:04:36,342 --> 01:04:38,932
- I'm Fauna.
- I'm Flora.

732
01:04:40,304 --> 01:04:43,524
I'm flattered. Excuse me, ladies.

733
01:04:48,687 --> 01:04:51,937
I can't find her anywhere.
Let's just leave.

734
01:04:52,358 --> 01:04:54,528
- Out the back.
- Now pull yourself together.

735
01:04:54,693 --> 01:04:56,443
She'll turn up, the little cockroach.

736
01:04:56,612 --> 01:04:58,572
You get to the party
or they'll suspect something.

737
01:04:58,656 --> 01:05:00,946
- I'll be down soon.
- Yes, Mother.

738
01:05:08,207 --> 01:05:11,327
Everyone, your attention, please.

739
01:05:15,840 --> 01:05:19,430
Tonight we dance
for our treasured guest of honor,

740
01:05:19,593 --> 01:05:21,093
Fester Addams.

741
01:05:23,681 --> 01:05:26,681
The mamushka!

742
01:05:28,352 --> 01:05:31,352
Taught to us by our Cossack cousins,

743
01:05:31,522 --> 01:05:34,442
the mamushka has been
an Addams' family tradition

744
01:05:34,608 --> 01:05:36,228
since God knows when.

745
01:05:36,402 --> 01:05:39,242
We danced the mamushka
while Nero fiddled.

746
01:05:39,405 --> 01:05:42,155
We danced the mamushka at Waterloo.

747
01:05:42,575 --> 01:05:46,535
We danced the mamushka
for Jack the Ripper.

748
01:05:47,204 --> 01:05:50,044
And now, Fester Addams,

749
01:05:50,583 --> 01:05:54,713
this mamushka is for you.

750
01:06:16,609 --> 01:06:21,109
- Where are you going? There's trouble.
- Hey! Not to worry. Plan B.

751
01:06:21,280 --> 01:06:23,780
- But that hideous little girl knows...
- I'm in charge.

752
01:06:23,949 --> 01:06:25,989
Ten minutes, I'll be back.

753
01:07:21,465 --> 01:07:24,215
Mamushka, mamushka

754
01:07:24,385 --> 01:07:25,835
He comes for his mamushka

755
01:07:26,011 --> 01:07:27,530
With a hey and a hey
and a hey and a hey

756
01:07:27,554 --> 01:07:30,644
And a hey and a hey
and a hey and a hey

757
01:07:30,808 --> 01:07:32,688
And a hey and a hey
and a hey and a hey and a...

758
01:07:33,060 --> 01:07:35,230
Wait!

759
01:07:37,356 --> 01:07:41,356
I swear by Mummy

760
01:07:41,527 --> 01:07:43,647
And Daddums

761
01:07:44,154 --> 01:07:46,994
This detestable Fester's

762
01:07:47,157 --> 01:07:50,657
The Echt Fester Addams

763
01:07:52,329 --> 01:07:56,039
So hey, hey, hey, hey
hey, hey, hey, hey

764
01:07:56,208 --> 01:07:59,998
Let's dance the dance of brotherly love!

765
01:08:00,170 --> 01:08:01,550
Mamushka!

766
01:08:05,217 --> 01:08:07,677
What the hell's going on over there?

767
01:08:07,845 --> 01:08:11,255
How would you like to be rid
of the Addamses for good?

768
01:08:12,224 --> 01:08:15,564
- I'm serious.
- What can I do for you?

769
01:08:17,730 --> 01:08:20,440
You are gonna love this.

770
01:08:23,360 --> 01:08:26,490
We've been married
for almost 20 years.

771
01:08:28,073 --> 01:08:30,283
Sometimes it seems like more.

772
01:08:33,245 --> 01:08:36,905
Well, people grow. People change.

773
01:08:47,760 --> 01:08:49,890
Isn't it a beautiful night?

774
01:08:54,725 --> 01:08:57,305
You'll come see me before you leave,
won't you, Fester?

775
01:08:57,478 --> 01:08:59,268
I'll call once I'm alone.

776
01:08:59,438 --> 01:09:01,518
There's your ride, girls.

777
01:09:13,494 --> 01:09:17,414
You're a marvelous dancer.
It's been such fun.

778
01:09:20,584 --> 01:09:23,294
I can't. We mustn't.

779
01:09:29,927 --> 01:09:30,967
Call me!

780
01:09:31,136 --> 01:09:33,136
Mamushka, mamushka

781
01:09:33,305 --> 01:09:35,635
I swallowed with one whoosh-ka!

782
01:09:35,808 --> 01:09:37,178
And a hey and a hey

783
01:09:37,351 --> 01:09:39,521
And a hey and a hey and a hey

784
01:09:40,145 --> 01:09:41,595
Hey, hey!

785
01:09:42,648 --> 01:09:45,818
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

786
01:09:45,984 --> 01:09:46,984
Gordon.

787
01:09:47,152 --> 01:09:48,152
Hey. Hey, hey

788
01:09:48,320 --> 01:09:49,320
Gordon, Gordon, stop it.

789
01:09:49,488 --> 01:09:50,488
Gordon, no.

790
01:09:50,656 --> 01:09:51,656
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey!

791
01:09:51,824 --> 01:09:52,824
Stop it, Gordon. Stop it!

792
01:09:52,991 --> 01:09:54,661
Stop it, this instant.

793
01:09:55,452 --> 01:09:58,662
- Is that lipstick all over your face?
- From the twins.

794
01:09:58,831 --> 01:10:01,581
The beauteous Amor twins.

795
01:10:01,750 --> 01:10:03,080
The twins?

796
01:10:03,252 --> 01:10:06,002
Gordon, I don't understand this.
Let me get this clear.

797
01:10:06,171 --> 01:10:10,131
- Have you been having a good time?
- Yes! I have!

798
01:10:10,300 --> 01:10:11,930
It was marvelous.

799
01:10:12,094 --> 01:10:15,934
I sang up a storm
and danced till I dropped!

800
01:10:16,181 --> 01:10:19,681
The mamushka! The mamushka!

801
01:10:19,852 --> 01:10:24,482
And a hey and a hey
and a hey and a hey and a hey

802
01:10:27,067 --> 01:10:29,567
- Mother?
- Mother? Mother? Who is that?

803
01:10:29,736 --> 01:10:32,776
- I don't think I recall.
- Mother, please.

804
01:10:32,948 --> 01:10:35,408
I'm just fine. I'm dandy.

805
01:10:35,826 --> 01:10:38,326
Don't concern yourself
about me, Gordon.

806
01:10:38,495 --> 01:10:41,615
Please, return to your depraved orgy.

807
01:10:42,249 --> 01:10:45,079
Sometimes I think
you're not even my son.

808
01:10:45,252 --> 01:10:48,252
- Don't say that.
- I'm just your mother.

809
01:10:48,422 --> 01:10:51,972
You only owe me
your entire existence on this planet.

810
01:10:52,426 --> 01:10:55,796
Please, Gordon, by all means,
go sing, dance, date.

811
01:10:55,971 --> 01:10:59,311
Oh, Mother, I'm so terribly sorry.

812
01:11:03,103 --> 01:11:05,653
It was just a party. It's over.

813
01:11:06,565 --> 01:11:08,185
It means nothing.

814
01:11:08,692 --> 01:11:12,032
The Siamese twins, the hunchback,
Cousin It,

815
01:11:12,654 --> 01:11:14,164
they're not you.

816
01:11:14,323 --> 01:11:16,823
Say it, Gordon. Make me believe it.

817
01:11:17,326 --> 01:11:20,656
I love you. And I want money.

818
01:11:21,330 --> 01:11:23,250
We've got to find Tully.

819
01:11:28,170 --> 01:11:30,710
Look, our little boy.

820
01:11:31,173 --> 01:11:32,673
All tuckered out.

821
01:11:32,841 --> 01:11:36,841
It's so sweet.
He looks just like a little entrée.

822
01:11:38,388 --> 01:11:41,518
- Where's the party?
- It's over, darling.

823
01:11:42,226 --> 01:11:46,016
- Have you seen your sister?
- Not since before the mamushka.

824
01:11:46,813 --> 01:11:47,983
Gomez.

825
01:11:48,649 --> 01:11:51,399
Fan out.
Pugsley, head for the dung heap.

826
01:11:51,568 --> 01:11:54,148
Mama and Morticia, the shallow graves.
I'll take the abyss.

827
01:11:54,321 --> 01:11:56,661
Lurch, check out the bottomless pit.

828
01:11:56,823 --> 01:11:58,413
- Fester?
- Up here!

829
01:11:58,992 --> 01:12:03,622
Fester, you take the ravine
and the unmarked abandoned well.

830
01:12:03,789 --> 01:12:07,749
Someone should stay behind
in case she comes back.

831
01:12:08,335 --> 01:12:10,085
Good man. Good thinking!

832
01:12:10,254 --> 01:12:12,384
Then who'll take the swamp?

833
01:12:15,717 --> 01:12:19,047
That's the spirit, Thing. Lend a hand.
Let's go!

834
01:12:26,395 --> 01:12:27,555
Gordon!

835
01:12:28,480 --> 01:12:30,020
Don't dawdle.

836
01:12:41,577 --> 01:12:44,367
- What are you doing?
- I'm relaxing.

837
01:12:45,497 --> 01:12:48,787
- Taking a little sun.
- Have you gone mad?

838
01:12:58,385 --> 01:13:06,385
Wednesday!

839
01:13:49,186 --> 01:13:52,356
- What is all this?
- This is a restraining order.

840
01:13:52,522 --> 01:13:54,192
- A restraining order?
- Yes.

841
01:13:54,358 --> 01:13:58,318
It requires you
to keep a distance of 1,000 yards

842
01:13:58,487 --> 01:13:59,487
from this house.

843
01:13:59,655 --> 01:14:01,855
I am restrained from my own house?

844
01:14:02,032 --> 01:14:04,662
Not your house, mustache.
Not anymore.

845
01:14:04,826 --> 01:14:07,326
It belongs to
the oldest living descendant,

846
01:14:07,496 --> 01:14:10,706
the elder brother, Fester Addams.

847
01:14:10,874 --> 01:14:14,004
- Fester adores Gomez.
- No, no, he's afraid of him.

848
01:14:14,169 --> 01:14:17,629
Seeing the twins brought it all back.
You're bitter rivals, Gomez.

849
01:14:17,798 --> 01:14:21,048
- I demand to speak with Fester.
- Sorry. No can do.

850
01:14:21,677 --> 01:14:24,137
He's very hurt. Just leave.

851
01:14:26,723 --> 01:14:29,023
But he isn't even Uncle Fester.

852
01:14:32,646 --> 01:14:35,686
Have no fear. Justice shall prevail.

853
01:14:36,233 --> 01:14:38,153
The courts will decide.

854
01:14:38,652 --> 01:14:42,492
They say a man who represents himself
has a fool for a client.

855
01:14:42,656 --> 01:14:44,986
Well, with God as my witness,

856
01:14:45,158 --> 01:14:47,198
I am that fool!

857
01:14:47,994 --> 01:14:52,164
Therefore, it is with no small amount
of personal satisfaction

858
01:14:52,749 --> 01:14:57,249
that I declare Fester Addams
legal executor of the Addams estate

859
01:14:57,504 --> 01:15:00,634
and rightful owner of all possessions

860
01:15:00,799 --> 01:15:04,839
and properties contained therein,
with one exception.

861
01:15:05,011 --> 01:15:06,801
Gomez Addams,

862
01:15:07,347 --> 01:15:11,227
I believe these are yours.

863
01:16:50,242 --> 01:16:53,582
- You are doing this on purpose.
- That's right, Mother. Isn't this fun?

864
01:16:53,745 --> 01:16:55,495
I'll race you back.

865
01:16:57,499 --> 01:17:00,079
Yes, we've been forced from our home.

866
01:17:00,710 --> 01:17:03,840
Yes, we've been betrayed
by those we trusted,

867
01:17:04,297 --> 01:17:07,717
but we are Addamses,
and we will not submit.

868
01:17:09,386 --> 01:17:12,636
Who recalls the fable
of The Tortoise and the Hare?

869
01:17:13,014 --> 01:17:16,234
The swift yet lazy little cottontail

870
01:17:16,393 --> 01:17:19,023
and his slow
but determined companion?

871
01:17:19,688 --> 01:17:21,308
What does this story teach us?

872
01:17:21,481 --> 01:17:24,281
Kill the hare! Skin it. Boil it.

873
01:17:24,442 --> 01:17:27,192
- Put the tortoise on the highway.
- During rush hour.

874
01:17:27,362 --> 01:17:30,282
Yes. We will survive.

875
01:17:30,991 --> 01:17:34,661
Poison us. Strangle us.
Break our bones.

876
01:17:34,828 --> 01:17:36,908
We will come back for more.

877
01:17:37,706 --> 01:17:39,076
And why?

878
01:17:39,249 --> 01:17:42,669
- Because we like it.
- Because we're Addamses.

879
01:17:42,836 --> 01:17:44,376
We're Addamses.

880
01:17:52,262 --> 01:17:54,312
Here, Lurch. On the house.

881
01:18:12,032 --> 01:18:15,492
We have so many homemakers
re-entering the workforce.

882
01:18:15,660 --> 01:18:18,500
Your domestic skills
can be very valuable.

883
01:18:18,663 --> 01:18:21,333
- College?
- Private tutors.

884
01:18:22,334 --> 01:18:24,504
- Major?
- Spells and hexes.

885
01:18:25,670 --> 01:18:27,170
Liberal Arts.

886
01:18:27,964 --> 01:18:31,344
What about your husband?
Is he currently employed?

887
01:18:32,594 --> 01:18:35,304
He's going through a bad patch
at the moment,

888
01:18:35,472 --> 01:18:36,972
but it's not his fault.

889
01:18:37,140 --> 01:18:38,640
Of course not.

890
01:18:39,809 --> 01:18:42,349
What is he, a loafer?
A hopeless layabout?

891
01:18:42,520 --> 01:18:44,310
A shiftless dreamer?

892
01:18:46,483 --> 01:18:47,943
Not anymore.

893
01:18:53,823 --> 01:18:56,663
- Is this made from real lemons?
- Yes.

894
01:18:56,993 --> 01:18:59,663
I only like all-natural
fruits and beverages

895
01:18:59,829 --> 01:19:02,619
organically grown with no preservatives.

896
01:19:02,958 --> 01:19:05,998
- Are you sure they're real lemons?
- Yes.

897
01:19:06,461 --> 01:19:08,501
Well, I'll tell you what.

898
01:19:08,672 --> 01:19:09,802
I'll buy a cup

899
01:19:09,965 --> 01:19:12,965
if you buy a box
of my delicious Girl Scout cookies.

900
01:19:13,134 --> 01:19:14,554
Do we have a deal?

901
01:19:14,719 --> 01:19:17,259
Are they made from real Girl Scouts?

902
01:19:29,526 --> 01:19:31,936
And so,
the witch lured Hansel and Gretel

903
01:19:32,112 --> 01:19:35,742
into the candy house
by promising them more sweets.

904
01:19:35,991 --> 01:19:38,281
And she told them to look in the oven.

905
01:19:38,451 --> 01:19:42,161
And she was about to push them in
when, lo and behold,

906
01:19:42,539 --> 01:19:45,619
Hansel pushed the poor,
defenseless witch

907
01:19:45,792 --> 01:19:49,502
into the oven instead,
where she was burned alive,

908
01:19:49,671 --> 01:19:51,341
writhing in agony.

909
01:19:54,551 --> 01:19:58,851
Now, boys and girls,
what do you think that feels like?

910
01:20:52,776 --> 01:20:54,436
Welcome to the show.

911
01:20:54,611 --> 01:20:56,422
Voodoo witch doctors
here in the United States.

912
01:20:56,446 --> 01:20:57,446
Here, kitty, kitty.

913
01:20:57,614 --> 01:21:01,994
Do they really exist
or is this just tabloid hooey?

914
01:21:02,160 --> 01:21:04,240
We'd love you to call in
with your comments.

915
01:21:06,998 --> 01:21:09,248
After lunch, we'll try again.

916
01:21:10,752 --> 01:21:12,172
Yes, Mother.

917
01:21:15,965 --> 01:21:17,965
We'll find the money.

918
01:21:18,760 --> 01:21:21,930
Meanwhile, we have this little nest,
quiet and cozy

919
01:21:22,097 --> 01:21:24,557
without that dreadful family.

920
01:21:25,975 --> 01:21:27,385
Yes, Mother.

921
01:21:28,061 --> 01:21:30,901
So, you claim that your son
was brainwashed

922
01:21:31,064 --> 01:21:34,904
by voodoo witch doctors
and forced to recruit others.

923
01:21:35,485 --> 01:21:36,565
Let's take a call.

924
01:21:36,736 --> 01:21:38,146
Hello, Sally.

925
01:21:38,321 --> 01:21:40,911
Mr. Addams, please stop calling.

926
01:21:41,407 --> 01:21:43,237
We do not know where they meet.

927
01:21:43,409 --> 01:21:45,409
Let's take another call.

928
01:21:47,080 --> 01:21:49,830
Gomez, why don't we go for a drive?

929
01:21:50,333 --> 01:21:52,423
- The whole family.
- A drive?

930
01:21:53,419 --> 01:21:56,459
- And miss Gilligan?
- Dinner's gonna be late.

931
01:21:57,257 --> 01:21:59,257
Here, boy. Here, boy.

932
01:22:07,517 --> 01:22:08,727
Gordon.

933
01:22:09,894 --> 01:22:11,154
Gordon!

934
01:23:18,463 --> 01:23:21,263
I would like to
speak with Fester, please.

935
01:23:30,099 --> 01:23:34,139
You're a desperate woman
consumed by greed and bitterness.

936
01:23:34,812 --> 01:23:37,982
- We could have been such friends.
- Gordon, let's get started.

937
01:23:38,149 --> 01:23:39,649
- But, Mother...
- Stop stalling.

938
01:23:39,817 --> 01:23:42,607
I'm not stalling. Stop badgering me.

939
01:23:44,989 --> 01:23:48,829
- The vault, Mrs. Addams, any thoughts?
- None whatsoever.

940
01:23:48,993 --> 01:23:51,123
Tully, take over. Tighten it.

941
01:23:51,287 --> 01:23:53,140
But I got this stomach thing
when I torture people.

942
01:23:53,164 --> 01:23:54,334
Do it.

943
01:23:57,794 --> 01:23:58,964
Again.

944
01:24:07,720 --> 01:24:09,050
Tighter.

945
01:24:13,226 --> 01:24:15,226
You've done this before.

946
01:25:02,608 --> 01:25:05,738
Who is it?
We're paid through Thursday.

947
01:25:06,863 --> 01:25:08,573
Morticia.

948
01:25:09,032 --> 01:25:12,242
Morticia. Morticia what?

949
01:25:12,994 --> 01:25:16,044
Slow down!
It's terrible when you stutter.

950
01:25:29,385 --> 01:25:33,635
Morticia in danger.

951
01:25:34,223 --> 01:25:35,393
Stop.

952
01:25:35,558 --> 01:25:39,638
Send help at once. Stop!

953
01:25:42,315 --> 01:25:44,975
You can't! Not with red-hot pokers!

954
01:25:45,902 --> 01:25:48,532
- Is this gonna smell?
- Tully Alford,

955
01:25:48,696 --> 01:25:52,066
charlatan, deadbeat, parasite.

956
01:25:53,159 --> 01:25:55,159
How Gomez adored you.

957
01:25:55,328 --> 01:25:57,658
Well, not enough.

958
01:25:58,623 --> 01:26:01,753
Morticia, please.

959
01:26:01,918 --> 01:26:05,628
And dear Fester, which is the real you?

960
01:26:06,422 --> 01:26:09,512
The loathsome,
underhanded monster you've become

961
01:26:09,967 --> 01:26:13,427
or the loathsome, underhanded monster
we came to love?

962
01:26:13,638 --> 01:26:14,848
Don't ask me.

963
01:26:32,532 --> 01:26:34,872
I know what you're feeling, Fester.

964
01:26:35,034 --> 01:26:36,284
Gordon!

965
01:26:37,537 --> 01:26:40,957
Gordon, I have a thought.
Just a notion, top of my head.

966
01:26:41,124 --> 01:26:42,964
Tell me what you think?

967
01:26:43,126 --> 01:26:46,626
Since you and Mrs. Addams
are so very close,

968
01:26:48,339 --> 01:26:49,969
be my guest.

969
01:26:52,677 --> 01:26:53,967
Addams!

970
01:26:56,305 --> 01:26:58,175
Darling, take care.

971
01:26:59,100 --> 01:27:01,940
Dirty pool, old man. Never again!

972
01:27:13,114 --> 01:27:14,784
One for you, Tully.

973
01:27:15,700 --> 01:27:17,030
And now...

974
01:27:27,086 --> 01:27:28,416
One for me.

975
01:27:28,588 --> 01:27:31,338
- Gomez, I'm on retainer.
- Let him up.

976
01:27:41,392 --> 01:27:44,232
That's right. Now get moving, Addams.

977
01:27:47,732 --> 01:27:49,612
Take him to the vault,

978
01:27:50,443 --> 01:27:52,993
and if you're not back in one hour,

979
01:27:53,779 --> 01:27:55,659
I displace her.

980
01:28:00,244 --> 01:28:03,124
Tish, seeing you like this,

981
01:28:03,289 --> 01:28:04,789
my blood boils.

982
01:28:04,957 --> 01:28:06,457
As does mine.

983
01:28:07,460 --> 01:28:10,460
- This wheel of pain.
- Our wheel.

984
01:28:10,630 --> 01:28:13,800
To live without you,
only that would be torture.

985
01:28:14,383 --> 01:28:17,893
A day alone, only that would be death.

986
01:28:20,223 --> 01:28:21,643
Knock it off.

987
01:28:23,476 --> 01:28:25,636
The vault, Addams, right now.

988
01:28:35,613 --> 01:28:38,413
- But, Mother, can't we...
- Can it, Gordon.

989
01:28:38,574 --> 01:28:41,914
Stop dragging your feet.
You disgust me!

990
01:28:42,620 --> 01:28:45,040
You're nothing
but a useless, sniveling baby.

991
01:28:45,206 --> 01:28:47,116
A stone around my neck.

992
01:28:47,458 --> 01:28:49,378
What was I thinking?

993
01:28:49,544 --> 01:28:51,294
I should have left you
where I found you.

994
01:28:52,588 --> 01:28:55,088
No tricks, Gomez!

995
01:28:56,050 --> 01:28:58,050
That's the wrong book.

996
01:29:07,311 --> 01:29:08,731
Allow me.

997
01:29:11,524 --> 01:29:13,234
Good show, old man.

998
01:29:15,987 --> 01:29:19,657
Put that book down, Gordon.
You don't know what it can do.

999
01:29:20,491 --> 01:29:23,871
- It's not just literature.
- Oh, really?

1000
01:29:25,871 --> 01:29:26,961
Quickly, darling.

1001
01:29:27,123 --> 01:29:29,123
Gordon, I'm your friend.

1002
01:29:29,542 --> 01:29:33,462
- Think of the doubloons.
- They're not yours, Tully.

1003
01:29:34,130 --> 01:29:35,130
Back off!

1004
01:29:35,298 --> 01:29:38,218
Leather straps. Red-hot pokers.

1005
01:29:38,843 --> 01:29:40,223
Later, my dearest.

1006
01:29:40,386 --> 01:29:43,216
Keep the book closed, Gordon.
Listen to Mother.

1007
01:29:43,389 --> 01:29:47,179
I'll never listen to you,
never ever again.

1008
01:29:47,351 --> 01:29:50,651
I had to be strict with you
because I cared. Put it down!

1009
01:29:50,813 --> 01:29:53,153
You never really loved me.

1010
01:29:53,566 --> 01:29:54,646
Fester, this way!

1011
01:29:54,817 --> 01:29:56,457
Stop whining,
you little good-for-nothing.

1012
01:29:56,485 --> 01:29:57,895
Be a man!

1013
01:29:58,404 --> 01:30:01,494
You were a terrible mother!

1014
01:30:02,074 --> 01:30:04,334
There! I said it.

1015
01:30:55,628 --> 01:30:57,128
Are they dead?

1016
01:30:57,505 --> 01:30:59,125
Does it matter?

1017
01:31:17,108 --> 01:31:18,818
Trick or...

1018
01:31:23,656 --> 01:31:25,116
Here we come!

1019
01:31:25,825 --> 01:31:28,365
- Pugsley, old man.
- Why, look at you.

1020
01:31:32,915 --> 01:31:34,325
How do you like it?

1021
01:31:36,127 --> 01:31:39,167
What can I say?
He's gonna break hearts.

1022
01:31:39,338 --> 01:31:40,918
Trick or treat.

1023
01:31:43,259 --> 01:31:45,509
Hello, Margaret. Cousin It.

1024
01:31:45,678 --> 01:31:48,968
- I almost didn't recognize you.
- Isn't he handsome?

1025
01:31:49,432 --> 01:31:52,562
Everyone keeps asking
where he bought his costume.

1026
01:31:52,727 --> 01:31:54,307
It is a wonderful hat.

1027
01:31:55,521 --> 01:31:58,481
What are you, darling?
Where's your costume?

1028
01:31:58,649 --> 01:32:01,149
This is my costume.
I'm a homicidal maniac.

1029
01:32:01,318 --> 01:32:03,698
They look just like everyone else.

1030
01:32:08,242 --> 01:32:11,622
I'm so glad
I can spend this night with my family,

1031
01:32:11,787 --> 01:32:13,657
now that I've got my memory back.

1032
01:32:13,831 --> 01:32:18,001
Thank God for that lightning.
Knocked some sense into you.

1033
01:32:21,130 --> 01:32:22,670
You remember, old man.

1034
01:32:22,840 --> 01:32:25,090
Dr. Pinder-Schloss
really did find Fester

1035
01:32:25,259 --> 01:32:27,929
tangled in a tuna net 25 years ago,

1036
01:32:28,471 --> 01:32:29,931
with amnesia.

1037
01:32:30,097 --> 01:32:32,137
From the Bermuda Triangle.

1038
01:32:35,519 --> 01:32:38,349
How true.
Stranger things have happened.

1039
01:32:38,522 --> 01:32:40,322
Please, Uncle Fester.

1040
01:32:41,150 --> 01:32:43,490
- Pugsley.
- For the picture.

1041
01:32:50,618 --> 01:32:53,948
All right, everybody, time for a game.

1042
01:32:54,288 --> 01:32:57,118
What shall it be? Bobbing for apples?

1043
01:32:57,291 --> 01:32:58,421
Charades?

1044
01:32:59,752 --> 01:33:02,212
Of course. Wake the dead.

1045
01:33:02,379 --> 01:33:05,759
- Wake the dead!
- Wake the dead!

1046
01:33:06,342 --> 01:33:08,222
Out to the cemetery!
Come on, everyone.

1047
01:33:08,385 --> 01:33:10,255
I've never played this before.

1048
01:33:10,429 --> 01:33:12,509
- How does it go?
- Did you bring a shovel?

1049
01:33:12,681 --> 01:33:15,601
- Uncle Fester, will you be on my team?
- No, mine.

1050
01:33:15,768 --> 01:33:17,528
I tell you what.
We'll give you a head start.

1051
01:33:17,603 --> 01:33:20,233
Three skulls and a pelvis. How is that?

1052
01:33:23,317 --> 01:33:26,067
My own dear brother.

1053
01:33:35,579 --> 01:33:37,909
- Come on.
- We'll catch up.

1054
01:33:41,627 --> 01:33:44,247
Wake the dead! Wake the dead!

1055
01:33:45,589 --> 01:33:47,469
Uncle Atlas, wake up.

1056
01:33:49,051 --> 01:33:52,431
- Come on, Aunt LaBorgia, wake up.
- No, no, no, children.

1057
01:33:52,596 --> 01:33:55,926
You have to dig. That's half the fun.

1058
01:34:07,444 --> 01:34:09,784
Oh, Tish, what more could we ask?

1059
01:34:12,366 --> 01:34:13,736
Gomez.

1060
01:34:19,790 --> 01:34:22,960
Cara Mia, is it true?

1061
01:34:23,627 --> 01:34:24,707
Oui.

1062
01:34:25,296 --> 01:34:26,586
Mon amour.

1063
01:34:37,808 --> 01:34:40,098
Wake up, Grandpa Addams.
It's Halloween.

1064
01:34:40,269 --> 01:34:42,729
Children, look! Great-Aunt Lavinia!

1065
01:34:42,897 --> 01:34:45,437
She was beheaded by her own children!

1066
01:34:45,608 --> 01:34:53,608
Yay!

